attachment.name: CNN and CNN en Español in Miami
attachment.caption:
Taking the political pulse in Miami in English and in Spanish ahead of the CNN #GOPdebate and the Florida primaries. 

Tomando el pulso en Miami, en inglés y español, antes del #GOPDebate y las primarias de Florida.

media.alt:
We’re here in Miami, taking the political pulse ahead of tonight’s CNN #GOPdebate, the last debate before the critical Florida primaries. We talked to Latino voters at Versailles, an iconic spot in Little Havana for the Cuban community, to students at the University of Miami and other voters in the city to find out what they think of this presidential election. We’ll be posting what we found on CNN and CNN en Español in English and in Spanish. #votalatino2016 #floridaprimary #politics

Estamos en Miami tomando el pulso político antes del debate presidencial republicano de CNN #GOPdebate esta noche, el último antes de las importantes primarias en Florida. Hablamos con la comunidad latina en lugares icónicos de la ciudad, entre ellos, el Café Versailles. Les preguntamos a los votantes lo que piensan de la elección presidencial. Iremos publicando lo que encontremos en CNN y CNNEE en inglés y español #VotoLatino2016 #FloridaPrimary

Bruna Barbosa, a University of Miami student who spoke with us yesterday, believes that in the end a rational Republican candidate will prevail.

(At tonight’s) debate "I think that John Kasich is going to win, cause he’s the most rational person in the Republican party." CNN en Español #votalatino2016 #floridaprimary #supertuesday #politics 

Bruna Barbosa, una estudiante de University of Miami que habló ayer con nosotros, cree que al final, se impondrá el candidato republicano "más racional".

"En el debate (de esta noche) creo que Kasich va a ganar porque es la persona más racional en el partido republicano".

Meet Humberto Pellon, 78. Like many of the Cuban-Americans we spoke with, this Miami resident is supporting Marco Rubio. As for Republican frontrunner Donald J. Trump? Pellon doesn't think very highly of him at all.

“I am going to vote for Marco Rubio because he is the best candidate of the Republican Party ... Almost everyone here is voting for him ... I don’t like Trump, he is a charlatan.” CNN en Español #votalatino2016 #floridaprimary #supertuesday #politics

Humberto Pellón tiene 78 años. Como muchos de los cubanoestadounidenses con los que hablamos, este residente de Miami apoya a Marco Rubio. ¿Y qué opina de Donald Trump? No tiene muy buen concepto de él.

“Voy a votar por Marco Rubio porque es el mejor de los candidatos del Partido Republicano... Por Rubio van a votar casi todos... A mí no me gusta Trump, es un charlatán”.

We caught a ride with Miami resident Duniel Menéndez, 30. He says while Donald J. Trump has been a financial success, he doesn’t believe the business mogul would make a good president. 

“He is only looking for popularity and he's a showman," he said. 

"I think Marco Rubio is a good politician, but he still needs a bit of experience to manage the biggest country in the world. I think he would be a good president but not at this moment but in a future." CNN en Español #votalatino2016 #floridaprimary #supertuesday #politics 

Nos subimos al taxi de Duniel Menéndez, un residente de Miami de 30 años. Dice que aunque Donald Trump ha logrado grandes éxitos en las finanzas, no cree que el magnate sería un buen presidente.

“Yo pienso que Marco Rubio es un buen político pero que le falta un poco de experiencia todavía como para manejar el país más grande del mundo, y yo creo que él sería un gran presidente pero no en este momento, sino en un futuro”.

message:
Taking the political pulse in Miami in English and in Spanish ahead of the CNN #GOPdebate and the Florida primaries. 

Tomando el pulso en Miami, en inglés y español, antes del #GOPDebate y las primarias de Florida.

attachment.name: CNN and CNN en Español in Miami
attachment.caption:
Taking the political pulse in Miami in English and in Spanish ahead of the CNN #GOPdebate and the Florida primaries. 

Tomando el pulso en Miami, en inglés y español, antes del #GOPDebate y las primarias de Florida.

media.alt:
Days before the critical battle for the Sunshine State, it's down to the wire for Donald J. Trump, Ted Cruz, Marco Rubio and John Kasich.  Meet Rita Betancourt, 70. She's #TeamRubio.

“I am going to vote for Marco Rubio, and if in the end he doesn’t make it, I will vote for the Republican that does. As for the debates, I would have liked that each republican candidate said what they would do if they were president and not argue as much.” CNN en Español #cnn #miami #versailles #votalatino2016 #floridaprimary #supertuesday #politics

Días antes de las cruciales primarias de Florida, llega la hora de la verdad para Donald Trump, Ted Cruz, Marco Rubio y John Kasich. Ella es Rita Betancourt, de 70, y apoya a Marco Rubio #TeamRubio.

“Yo voy a votar por Marco Rubio y si a la final no va Marco Rubio, yo voto por el republicano que vaya. Referente a los debates, lo que puedo decir, es que a mi me hubiera gustado que cada uno de ellos dijera lo que iba a hacer si era presidente y no que discutieran tanto.”

Ahead of tonight's #gopdebate and #floridaprimary, Miami resident Julia Mendez, 21, is #TeamRubio.  CNN en Español  #miami #politics #supertuesday

"I think that Marco Rubio is a potential candidate for the Republicans, his views are more, they’re more of like political compared to like Donald J. Trump who’s more of like a businessman, and I feel like he’s not very credible compared to the other candidates."

Antes del #gopdebate de esta noche y las primarias de Florida, la residente de Miami Julia Méndez de 21 años es #EquipoRubio

“Yo creo que Marco Rubio es un potencial candidato para los republicanos. Sus opiniones son mas políticas en comparación a las de Donald Trump quién es mas un hombre de negocios. Siento que el no es creíble en comparación a los otros candidatos.”

For Emilio Alvarez, 72, a Cuban-American living in the United States for 52 years, this campaign has been unlike any other. 

“This political campaign has been a completely different animal. There exists a moment in time where the necessity of the people leads to populism, and populism is being manifested in Bernie Sanders and in Donald J. Trump. When Trump makes is presentation he doesn’t say how he is going to resolve things. He says he will change things, and “Make America Great” but not how he will do it. I am an independent and currently cannot vote for the Republicans. CNN en Español #cnn #miami #versailles #votalatino2016 #floridaprimary #supertuesday #politics

Para Emilio Àlvarez, un cubanoestadunidense de 72 años que ha vivido en los Estados Unidos por 52 años, esta campaña ha sido como ninguna otra.

“Esta campaña política ha sido un animal totalmente diferente a las anteriores. La actitud de votantes basado en muchas cosas, sea personas que están sin trabajo, personas a quien la economía ha maltratado – están angustiados y molestos. Existe un momento donde la necesitad lleva al populismo. El populismo se esta manifestando en Sanders y en Trump. En sus presentaciones el señor Trump no dice como va a resolver las cosas, el dice que va a cambiar las cosas y “Make America Great” pero no dice como lo va hacer.”

Bruna Barbosa, a University of Miami student who spoke with us yesterday, believes that in the end a rational Republican candidate will prevail.

(At tonight’s) debate "I think that John Kasich is going to win, cause he’s the most rational person in the Republican party." CNN en Español #votalatino2016 #floridaprimary #supertuesday #politics 

Bruna Barbosa, una estudiante de University of Miami que habló ayer con nosotros, cree que al final, se impondrá el candidato republicano "más racional".

"En el debate (de esta noche) creo que Kasich va a ganar porque es la persona más racional en el partido republicano".

Meet Humberto Pellon, 78. Like many of the Cuban-Americans we spoke with, this Miami resident is supporting Marco Rubio. As for Republican frontrunner Donald J. Trump? Pellon doesn't think very highly of him at all.

“I am going to vote for Marco Rubio because he is the best candidate of the Republican Party ... Almost everyone here is voting for him ... I don’t like Trump, he is a charlatan.” CNN en Español #votalatino2016 #floridaprimary #supertuesday #politics

Humberto Pellón tiene 78 años. Como muchos de los cubanoestadounidenses con los que hablamos, este residente de Miami apoya a Marco Rubio. ¿Y qué opina de Donald Trump? No tiene muy buen concepto de él.

“Voy a votar por Marco Rubio porque es el mejor de los candidatos del Partido Republicano... Por Rubio van a votar casi todos... A mí no me gusta Trump, es un charlatán”.

Polish-born French physicist Marie Curie (1867-1934) discovered polonium and radium. Her work led to the creation of X-rays -- a crucial component of modern-day medicine. She was the first woman to win a Nobel Prize and the only woman to win this award in two categories: Physics and Chemistry.

See the full list here: http://cnn.it/1UPTCsg

American marine biologist and conservationist Rachel Carson (1907-1964) was also an author. After WWII, she focused on warning the public about the long-term effects of misusing pesticides. Her book Silent Spring and other works challenged the practices of agricultural scientists and are credited with advancing the global environmental movement.

See the full list here: http://cnn.it/1UPTCsg

British chemist, crystallographer and biophysicist Rosalind Franklin (1920-1958) was the first to hypothesize and show, through x-ray diffraction, the double helix structure of DNA. Her discovery laid the ground work for Francis Crick and James Watson's molecular model of DNA. The Nobel Prize can only be shared by three living scientists and so Franklin was barely acknowledged when it was awarded to Watson, Crick and Maurice Wilkins for the discovery of the double-helix in 1962.

See the full list here: http://cnn.it/1UPTCsg

British primatologist Dame Jane Goodall, 81, is best known for her long-term research on wild chimpanzees in Tanzania. She founded, the Jane Goodall Institute Research Center in Gombe National Park, which is the world's longest running continuous wildlife research project. She also started Roots & Shoots, the Institute's global environmental and humanitarian program for young people.

See the full list here: http://cnn.it/1UPTCsg

Hong Kong Chinese and Canadian physician Margaret Chan OBE, 68, is Director-General of the World Health Organisation (WHO). She began her career in public health with the Hong Kong Department of Health where she was appointed Director in 1994. Three years later, while in this role, she handled the first human outbreak of H5N1 Avian Influenza and in 2003 successfully combated severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS) in Hong Kong.

See the full list here: http://cnn.it/1UPTCsg

Italian particle physicist Fabiola Gianotti, 53, is the first female Director-General of the European Organisation for Nuclear Research (CERN) and led the institution during the recent discovery of the Higgs boson as part of the ATLAS experiment.

See the full list here: http://cnn.it/1UPTCsg

message: This International Women's Day, we're celebrating women in science. See the full list: http://cnn.it/1UPTCsg

attachment.name: iReport.com Launches
attachment.caption: iReport.com Launches
attachment.description: CNN Worldwide launched iReport.com, its first uncensored, unfiltered, unedited, user-generated community Web site. iReport.com provides users with an open forum and a set of tools and applications to upload, share and discuss news with each other.

attachment.name: Most Watched Telecast - DNC
attachment.caption: Most Watched Telecast - DNC
attachment.description: For the final night of the Democratic National Convention on Aug. 28, CNN’s 10 p.m. hour ranked as the most watched telecast on all of U.S. television with more than 8 million viewers. This is the first time a cable news network has achieved this claim.

media.alt: For the final night of the Democratic National Convention on Aug. 28, CNN’s 10 p.m. hour ranked as the most watched telecast on all of U.S. television with more than 8 million viewers. This is the first time a cable news network has achieved this claim.

attachment.name: CNN Heroes: All-Star Tribute Gala
attachment.caption: CNN Heroes: All-Star Tribute Gala
attachment.description: The CNN Heroes initiative to recognize ordinary people who accomplish extraordinary deeds culminates with an all-star tribute gala in New York City.

attachment.name: Presidential Debate
attachment.caption: Presidential Debate
attachment.description: CNN hosts two presidential primary debates that became the two most-watched primary debates in cable news history.  The second CNN/YouTube debate – a showdown in St. Petersburg, Fla., among Republican contenders – had more than 4.4 million viewers, while a Democratic debate in Las Vegas averaged more than 4 million viewers.

attachment.name: CNN HD Launch
attachment.caption: CNN HD Launch
attachment.description: CNN launches CNN HD, its first 24-hour domestic news network in high definition.

media.alt: CNN launches CNN HD, its first 24-hour domestic news network in high definition.

attachment.name: CNN/Youtube Presidential Debate
attachment.caption: CNN/Youtube Presidential Debate
attachment.description: CNN and YouTube sponsor the first presidential debate to feature video questions provided directly from the American public. The Democratic debate in Charleston, S.C. won acclaim and scored record ratings for a presidential primary debate.

attachment.name: VA Tech Shooting
attachment.caption: VA Tech Shooting
attachment.description: A student from Virginia Tech goes on a shooting rampage at the university, killing 32 people and himself. It is the deadliest shooting by a single gunman in U.S. history.

attachment.name: Larry King- 50th Anniversary
attachment.caption: Larry King- 50th Anniversary
attachment.description: Larry King marks his 50th anniversary in broadcasting.

attachment.name: CNN iReport Launch
attachment.caption: CNN iReport Launch
attachment.description: CNN launches iReport, an invitation to its audience to participate in the news by sharing stories, videos, and photos of events near them. Today, iReport is the largest and most active user-generated news community in traditional media.

attachment.name: Hurricane Katrina
attachment.caption: Hurricane Katrina
attachment.description: CNN provided unmatched coverage of the devastation caused by Hurricane Katrina before and after it made landfall on Monday, August 29, 2005, demonstrating once again its power as a breaking news network and the premier source for news and updates long after the U.S. Gulf Coast felt the full force of the hurricane. The following month, the network opened its Gulf Coast bureau.

attachment.name: CNN on Jeopardy!
attachment.caption: CNN on Jeopardy!
attachment.description: Jeopardy! celebrates CNN’s 25th anniversary with a “CNN25” category.

media.alt: Jeopardy! celebrates CNN’s 25th anniversary with a “CNN25” category.

attachment.name: Tsunami
attachment.caption: Tsunami
attachment.description: A powerful earthquake strikes the Indian Ocean, triggering tsunamis that kill more than 200,000 people in nations from Sri Lanka to Indonesia.

attachment.name: 2004 Presidential Elections
attachment.caption: 2004 Presidential Elections
attachment.description: CNN.com reports record traffic on Election Day as it posts a new one-day high of more than 372 million page views, besting its one-day record on Sept. 12, 2001 when it recorded approximately 307 million page views. From 4 p.m. Nov. 2 until 4 p.m. Nov. 3, the site attracted another all-time high of approximately 650 million page views.

attachment.name: Sadaam Hussein's Capture
attachment.caption: Sadaam Hussein's Capture
attachment.description: CNN is the first to broadcast that Saddam Hussein was found hiding in a spider-hole outside of Tikrit, Iraq.  CNN’s coverage includes exclusive video of soldiers celebrating his capture.

attachment.name: Iraq War Begins
attachment.caption: Iraq War Begins
attachment.description: CNN, alone, reports live from Baghdad on the night the war on Iraq begins, with a record U.S. audience and a worldwide audience of nearly 1 billion, the largest audience of a non-sporting event in television history. U.S.-led coalition forces attack Iraq, which includes the large-scale bombing of Baghdad, Iraq. The campaign is dubbed "shock and awe."

attachment.name: Live Desert Surgery
attachment.caption: Live Desert Surgery
attachment.description: Medical and journalism history were made when CNN’s senior medical correspondent Dr. Sanjay Gupta reported live during a surgery that was being performed in the desert. Gupta’s live reports were the first-ever of a battlefield surgery.

attachment.name: Columbia Shuttle Disaster
attachment.caption: Columbia Shuttle Disaster
attachment.description: Space shuttle Columbia disintegrates as it returns to Earth, killing all seven astronauts aboard. CNN breaks news.

attachment.name: CNN.Com International Edition Launches
attachment.caption: CNN.Com International Edition Launches
attachment.description: CNN.com launches its all-encompassing international Web site, CNN.com International Edition. The English-language site serves up the top news stories in the international agenda to a global audience.

media.alt: CNN.com launches its all-encompassing international Web site, CNN.com International Edition. The English-language site serves up the top news stories in the international agenda to a global audience.

attachment.name: Olympic Park Bomber's Capture
attachment.caption: Olympic Park Bomber's Capture
attachment.description: CNN breaks capture of Eric Robert Rudolph. Even before the FBI or Justice Department were aware, CNN went on the air to break the news that Rudolph, the Olympic Park bomber, had been captured.

attachment.name: Connie Chung Tonight Debuts
attachment.caption: Connie Chung Tonight Debuts
attachment.description: At 8 p.m. on Monday, June 24, Connie Chung Tonight debuts with veteran journalist, Connie Chung at helm.

attachment.name: CNNRadio Noticias becomes CNN en Espanol Radio
attachment.caption: CNNRadio Noticias becomes CNN en Espanol Radio
attachment.description: CNNRadio Noticias celebrates its 20th anniversary and moves into a new multi-million-dollar, state-of-the-art studio. It also changes its name to CNN en Español Radio.

attachment.name: Crossfire Relaunch
attachment.caption: Crossfire Relaunch
attachment.description: CNN relaunches veteran political show Crossfire under new format and with new co-hosts: Democratic strategists James Carville and Paul Begala.

attachment.name: Strike on Afghanistan
attachment.caption: Strike on Afghanistan
attachment.description: President Bush announces strikes against "terrorist camps of al Qaeda, and the military installations of the Taliban regime in Afganistan."

media.alt: President Bush announces strikes against "terrorist camps of al Qaeda, and the military installations of the Taliban regime in Afganistan."

attachment.description: Nineteen hijackers commandeered four planes -- two fly into the twin towers in New York, one crashes into the Pentagon and another crashes into the ground in rural Pennsylvania.

attachment.name: China Hostages Release
attachment.caption: China Hostages Release
attachment.description: CNN airs live coverage of release of hostages from spy plane in China. Using a videophone, a sophisticated device that can compress video digitally, CNN is the only broadcaster that transmits live images of the liberation of American hostages.

attachment.name: Time Warner & AOL Merger
attachment.caption: Time Warner & AOL Merger
attachment.description: CNN parent company Time Warner, Inc., merges with America Online.

media.alt: CNN parent company Time Warner, Inc., merges with America Online.

attachment.name: North Korea Workers' Party Anniversary
attachment.caption: North Korea Workers' Party Anniversary
attachment.description: CNN is only western news organization to report live from North Korea for 55th anniversary of Workers’ Party of Korea, marking Mike Chinoy’s 12th visit to the communist nation.

media.alt: CNN is only western news organization to report live from North Korea for 55th anniversary of Workers’ Party of Korea, marking Mike Chinoy’s 12th visit to the communist nation.

attachment.name: CNN turns 20
attachment.caption: CNN turns 20
attachment.description: CNN celebrates 20th anniversary.

attachment.name: President Bush Elected
attachment.caption: President Bush Elected
attachment.description: The race for U.S. president between Al Gore and George W. Bush is extraordinarily close. A protracted presidential battle over Florida's votes ends up in the U.S. Supreme Court. Gore's concession and Bush's victory comes more than a month later. CNN is the most-watched cable news network during Election 2000 and its controversial aftermath.

attachment.name: Indian Airlines
attachment.caption: Indian Airlines
attachment.description: CNN provides exclusive live coverage of the release of 155 Indian Airlines hostages, including live pictures of the hijackers.

media.alt: CNN provides exclusive live coverage of the release of 155 Indian Airlines hostages, including live pictures of the hijackers.

attachment.name: Massacre in Izbica, Kosovo
attachment.caption: Massacre in Izbica, Kosovo
attachment.description: CNN and TIME obtains exclusive footage of massacre in Izbica, Kosovo, which is later used in U.S. State Department briefing on mass graves in the area to corroborate satellite photographs.

media.alt: CNN and TIME obtains exclusive footage of massacre in Izbica, Kosovo, which is later used in U.S. State Department briefing on mass graves in the area to corroborate satellite photographs.

attachment.name: Columbine
attachment.caption: Columbine
attachment.description: Two students kill and wound classmates and faculty before killing themselves at Columbine High School in Colorado.

attachment.name: Kosovo War (March 24 - June 10, 1999)
attachment.caption: Kosovo War (March 24 - June 10, 1999)

attachment.name: The Starr Report
attachment.caption: The Starr Report
attachment.description: Congress releases the "Starr Report," which alleges President Clinton lied under oath about his affair with White House intern Monica Lewinsky. The month before, Clinton addressed the nation after testifying for five and a half hours before Ken Starr's grand jury.

attachment.name: Paula Jones' Lawsuit Dismissed
attachment.caption: Paula Jones' Lawsuit Dismissed
attachment.description: CNN breaks the story of a Little Rock, Ark., judge dismissing the lawsuit by Paula Jones against President Bill Clinton.

attachment.name: Princess Diana Funeral
attachment.caption: Princess Diana Funeral
attachment.description: Princess Diana and Dodi Fayed die in a traffic accident in a Paris tunnel, sparking an outpouring of media coverage.

attachment.name: Hong Kong Handover
attachment.caption: Hong Kong Handover

attachment.name: CNN en Español
attachment.caption: CNN en Español
attachment.description: CNN launches CNN en Español network.

attachment.name: CNN/SI: CNN and Sports Illustrated
attachment.caption: CNN/SI: CNN and Sports Illustrated
attachment.description: CNN launches CNN/SI, a joint venture between CNN and Sports Illustrated.

media.alt: CNN launches CNN/SI, a joint venture between CNN and Sports Illustrated.

attachment.name: Turner and Time Warner, Inc.
attachment.caption: Turner and Time Warner, Inc.
attachment.description: CNN's parent company, Turner Broadcasting, is acquired by Time Warner, Inc.

media.alt: CNN's parent company, Turner Broadcasting, is acquired by Time Warner, Inc.

attachment.name: Dolly the Sheep
attachment.caption: Dolly the Sheep
attachment.description: The cloning of Dolly the sheep

media.alt: The cloning of Dolly the sheep

attachment.name: CNN.com
attachment.caption: CNN.com
attachment.description: CNN launches CNN.com, a multimedia news service on the Internet, making it the only site with a 24-hour, full-time staff reporting constantly updated news augmented by video, sound clips, still photographs, maps, and text.

media.alt: CNN launches CNN.com, a multimedia news service on the Internet, making it the only site with a 24-hour, full-time staff reporting constantly updated news augmented by video, sound clips, still photographs, maps, and text.

attachment.name: Civil War Between Serbs, Croats, and Muslims
attachment.caption: Civil War Between Serbs, Croats, and Muslims
attachment.description: Full-scale civil war breaks out in Bosnia and Herzegovina between Serbs, Croats, and Muslims. As part of an ethnic cleansing policy by the Serbs, thousands of Muslims are forced from towns and killed, or placed in concentration camps.

attachment.name: Oklahoma City Bombing
attachment.caption: Oklahoma City Bombing
attachment.description: The bombing of a federal office building in Oklahoma City, Oklahoma killed 168 people and wounded several more. Timothy McVeigh is eventually convicted on federal murder charges and executed in 2001.

attachment.name: TalkBack Live
attachment.caption: TalkBack Live
attachment.description: CNN premieres its first live interactive talk show, TalkBack Live.

attachment.name: O.J. Simpson Slow-Speed Chase
attachment.caption: O.J. Simpson Slow-Speed Chase
attachment.description: A slow-speed chase in a white Ford Bronco driven by O.J. Simpson captivates the nation on live television. Simpson is acquitted of the murders of his wife and her friend in October 1995.

attachment.name: Rwanda Genocide (April - June 1994)
attachment.caption: Rwanda Genocide (April - June 1994)

attachment.name: NAFTA Debate: Al Gore and Ross Perot
attachment.caption: NAFTA Debate: Al Gore and Ross Perot
attachment.description: CNN obtains record ratings for the Larry King Live NAFTA debate between Vice President Al Gore and Reform Party presidential candidate Ross Perot.

attachment.name: The End of the Branch Davidians
attachment.caption: The End of the Branch Davidians
attachment.description: A standoff in Waco, Texas, ends between federal agents and Branch Davidian members after 51 days. The siege ends with a fire and the deaths of group leader David Koresh and more than 80 of his followers.

attachment.name: CNN International Reaches 60 Million Households
attachment.caption: CNN International Reaches 60 Million Households
attachment.description: CNN International reaches 60 million households, matching CNN audience in the United States.

media.alt: CNN International reaches 60 million households, matching CNN audience in the United States.

attachment.name: Ross Perot's Presidential Bid
attachment.caption: Ross Perot's Presidential Bid
attachment.description: Ross Perot unveils plans for presidential bid on CNN’s Larry King Live.

attachment.name: Coup D’Etat in the Soviet Union
attachment.caption: Coup D’Etat in the Soviet Union
attachment.description: CNN is first with news and live pictures of coup d’etat in the Soviet Union and airs first live interviews with Mikhail Gorbachev, Boris Yeltsin and other Russian leaders.

media.alt: CNN is first with news and live pictures of coup d’etat in the Soviet Union and airs first live interviews with Mikhail Gorbachev, Boris Yeltsin and other Russian leaders.

attachment.name: Live Reports from Iran
attachment.caption: Live Reports from Iran
attachment.description: CNN is the first television network to broadcast live reports from Iran.

media.alt: CNN is the first television network to broadcast live reports from Iran.

attachment.name: CNN and CNN International Reach 100 Countries
attachment.caption: CNN and CNN International Reach 100 Countries

attachment.name: Iraq Invades Kuwait: Operation Desert Shield
attachment.caption: Iraq Invades Kuwait: Operation Desert Shield
attachment.description: Iraq invades Kuwait, provoking Operation Desert Shield, the U.S.-led military buildup of arms and troops in the Persian Gulf. Kuwait is eventually freed from Iraqi occupation, but Saddam Hussein remains in power.

attachment.name: Nelson Mandela Freed from Prison
attachment.caption: Nelson Mandela Freed from Prison
attachment.description: Anti-apartied champion Nelson Mandela is freed from prison in South Africa, after serving 27 years for opposing a government that sought to enforce severe segregation laws with brutality.

attachment.name: CNN and CNN Headline News Reaches Record
attachment.caption: CNN and CNN Headline News Reaches Record
attachment.description: CNN and CNN Headline News’ combined share of U.S. news-viewing audience reaches record of 28.4 percent (leading ABC, CBS and NBC).

media.alt: CNN and CNN Headline News’ combined share of U.S. news-viewing audience reaches record of 28.4 percent (leading ABC, CBS and NBC).

attachment.name: Fall of the Berlin Wall
attachment.caption: Fall of the Berlin Wall
attachment.description:
The East German Communist regime collapses. Crowds knock down parts of the Berlin Wall, the symbol of a Germany divided since World War II.
CNN provides history-defining footage of the fall of the Berlin Wall.

attachment.name: San Francisco Earthquake
attachment.caption: San Francisco Earthquake
attachment.description: Record number of households watch CNN’s San Francisco earthquake coverage.

media.alt: Record number of households watch CNN’s San Francisco earthquake coverage.

attachment.name: CNN Becomes Available Worldwide 24/7
attachment.caption: CNN Becomes Available Worldwide 24/7
attachment.description: CNN becomes available worldwide 24 hours a day with transmission on a Soviet satellite to Africa, the Middle East, the Indian subcontinent and Southeast Asia.

media.alt: CNN becomes available worldwide 24 hours a day with transmission on a Soviet satellite to Africa, the Middle East, the Indian subcontinent and Southeast Asia.

attachment.name: Tiananmen Square Demonstrations
attachment.caption: Tiananmen Square Demonstrations
attachment.description: Pro-democracy demonstrations in China are crushed in Beijing's Tiananmen Square.

attachment.name: Pan Am Flight 103 Explodes
attachment.caption: Pan Am Flight 103 Explodes
attachment.description: Pan Am Flight 103 exploded over Lockerbie.

attachment.name: Inside Politics '88 Debuts
attachment.caption: Inside Politics '88 Debuts
attachment.description: Network television’s only daily newscast devoted exclusively to American politics, CNN’s Inside Politics '88, debuts.

media.alt: Network television’s only daily newscast devoted exclusively to American politics, CNN’s Inside Politics '88, debuts.

attachment.name: CNN World Report
attachment.caption: CNN World Report
attachment.description: World’s first global newscast, CNN World Report, premieres with unedited, uncensored news reports from broadcasters in 100 countries.

attachment.name: Explosion at Chernobyl, Ukraine Power Plant
attachment.caption: Explosion at Chernobyl, Ukraine Power Plant
attachment.description: A Soviet nuclear reactor explodes at a power plant in Chernobyl, Ukraine, spreading radioactive fallout across Europe.

media.alt: A Soviet nuclear reactor explodes at a power plant in Chernobyl, Ukraine, spreading radioactive fallout across Europe.

attachment.name: The "Iran-Contra" Affair
attachment.caption: The "Iran-Contra" Affair
attachment.description: In the "Iran-Contra" affair, it's revealed the United States sold arms to Iran and used the money to finance Nicaraguan Contra insurgents. The political scandal dogs President Reagan in his second term.

media.alt: In the "Iran-Contra" affair, it's revealed the United States sold arms to Iran and used the money to finance Nicaraguan Contra insurgents. The political scandal dogs President Reagan in his second term.

attachment.name: Challenger Explosion
attachment.caption: Challenger Explosion
attachment.description: Space shuttle Challenger explodes on takeoff, killing all seven astronauts on board. CNN is the only network to air live coverage of explosion of the space shuttle challenger.

attachment.name: CNNI: 24 hours to Europe
attachment.caption: CNNI: 24 hours to Europe
attachment.description: CNN International begins live 24-hour transmission to Europe.

media.alt: CNN International begins live 24-hour transmission to Europe.

attachment.caption: Indira Gandhi Assasination

attachment.caption: Mexico City Earthquake

UPDATED: What we know about the EgyptAir flight MS181 hijacking 

-- Egypt corrects hijacker's name: He is Seif El Din Mustafa, an Egyptian national, Egypt officials say. It is NOT an American-Egyptian national named Ibrahim Samaha, as they previously stated.
--He hijacked the plane over his ex-wife, according to Cyprus officials
--He claims to have an explosive belt, but Egypt officials "doubt" it's true
--There are conflicting reports about the number of people on the plane when it was hijacked: Egypt said 55, Cyprus said 72, and the airline said 81.
--Most passengers have been allowed to deplane, but some passengers and crew remain on board

LIVE UPDATES: http://cnn.it/1ZHXNGY

message:

- The U.S. Capitol was on lockdown following reports of shots fired.
- Male suspect was shot at the U.S. Capitol complex by U.S. Capitol Police, now in custody.
- Suspect identified as Larry Russell Dawson, 66, of Tennessee, sources say.
- A female civilian bystander was injured by shrapnel, but no U.S. Capitol Police officers have been injured.

media.alt:
UPDATED: What we know about the EgyptAir flight MS181 hijacking 

-- Egypt corrects hijacker's name: He is Seif El Din Mustafa, an Egyptian national, Egypt officials say. It is NOT an American-Egyptian national named Ibrahim Samaha, as they previously stated.
--He hijacked the plane over his ex-wife, according to Cyprus officials
--He claims to have an explosive belt, but Egypt officials "doubt" it's true
--There are conflicting reports about the number of people on the plane when it was hijacked: Egypt said 55, Cyprus said 72, and the airline said 81.
--Most passengers have been allowed to deplane, but some passengers and crew remain on board

LIVE UPDATES: http://cnn.it/1ZHXNGY

message:
UPDATE:
- The U.S. Capitol was on lockdown following reports of shots fired.
- Male suspect was shot at the U.S. Capitol complex by U.S. Capitol Police, now in custody.
- Suspect identified as Larry Russell Dawson, 66, of Tennessee, sources say.
- A female civilian bystander was injured by shrapnel, but no U.S. Capitol Police officers have been injured.
- White House was also briefly locked down after what appears to be an unrelated incident.

media.alt:
UPDATED: What we know about the EgyptAir flight MS181 hijacking 

-- Egypt corrects hijacker's name: He is Seif El Din Mustafa, an Egyptian national, Egypt officials say. It is NOT an American-Egyptian national named Ibrahim Samaha, as they previously stated.
--He hijacked the plane over his ex-wife, according to Cyprus officials
--He claims to have an explosive belt, but Egypt officials "doubt" it's true
--There are conflicting reports about the number of people on the plane when it was hijacked: Egypt said 55, Cyprus said 72, and the airline said 81.
--Most passengers have been allowed to deplane, but some passengers and crew remain on board

LIVE UPDATES: http://cnn.it/1ZHXNGY

media.alt: U.S. Capitol police shot a male suspect Monday afternoon following reports of gunfire at the Capitol Visitors Center, law enforcement officials said.

message:
UPDATE:
- The U.S. Capitol was on lockdown following reports of shots fired.
- Male suspect was shot at the U.S. Capitol complex by U.S. Capitol Police, now in custody.
- Suspect identified as Larry Russell Dawson, 66, of Tennessee, sources say.
- A female civilian bystander was injured by shrapnel, but no U.S. Capitol Police officers have been injured.
- White House was also briefly locked down after what appears to be an unrelated incident.

––
